cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the task of nuclei detection in histology images using deep learning methods, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of Mixture Density Networks (MDNs) for this task also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the proposed modified cost function and the combination of probability maps could also relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
